data.content:
The root cause is that `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1 and rewrites the object model. Here are the three breaking changes in your code and the fixes:

---

## 1. `OpenApiString` removed (`Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace gone)

Schema examples are now `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead of `IOpenApiAny`.

```diff
- using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
+ using System.Text.Json.Nodes;

- param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");
+ param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

## 2. Security scheme references use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`

Instead of creating an `OpenApiSecurityScheme` with a nested `OpenApiReference`, use the new `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` type (which takes the scheme ID and the document):

```diff
- var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
- {
-     Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
- };
- operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
- {
-     new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
- };
+ var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", context.Document);
+ operation.Security = [new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
+ {
+     [oAuthScheme] = scopes
+ }];
```

> `context.Document` is available on the operation transformer context in .NET 10.

---

## 3. `Schema.Nullable` removed (OpenAPI 3.1 uses type arrays)

OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the `type` keyword (e.g., `["string", "null"]`). The `Nullable` property no longer exists. Use the `JsonSchemaType` flags enum:

```diff
- if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
-     property.Value.Nullable = false;
+ if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true
+     && property.Value.Type.HasValue)
+ {
+     property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
+ }
```

`JsonSchemaType` is in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models` (already imported).

---

## Final corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", context.Document);
    operation.Security = [new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
    {
        [oAuthScheme] = scopes
    }];

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true
                && property.Value.Type.HasValue)
            {
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

